---
import SectionHeading from "./SectionHeading.astro";
---

<section class="section mirror" id="mirror">
  <div class="container">
    <SectionHeading title="The same reviewers, locally and in CI.">
      A reviewer is a fitness function the author can optimize against before
      anyone opens a PR. The same reviewers run in your local loop (fast,
      pre-PR) and in CI (authoritative). CI runs the same gate, so its result
      matches what the author already saw.
    </SectionHeading>

    <div class="mirror-grid" data-reveal>
      <article class="surface">
        <div class="surface-head">
          <span class="surface-tag">local</span>
          <h3>The author loop</h3>
        </div>
        <p class="surface-copy">
          An authoring agent runs <span class="mono">bastion review</span> against
          the working tree, exactly as CI would, and loops until green.
        </p>
        <pre class="term"><code><span class="term-com"># fix what blocked, then run again</span>
<span class="term-prompt">$</span> <span class="term-cmd">while ! bastion review --base main; do</span>
<span class="term-prompt"> </span>   <span class="term-cmd">agent fixes the blocking findings</span>
<span class="term-prompt">$</span> <span class="term-cmd">done</span>
<span class="term-out term-out--pass">all gates pass &middot; ready to open a PR</span></code></pre>
      </article>

      <div class="mirror-link" aria-hidden="true">
        <span class="mirror-link-line"></span>
        <span class="mirror-link-chip">same reviewers.yaml</span>
        <span class="mirror-link-line"></span>
      </div>

      <article class="surface">
        <div class="surface-head">
          <span class="surface-tag">ci</span>
          <h3>The confirmation</h3>
        </div>
        <p class="surface-copy">
          On the PR, the same gate runs as the authoritative check. Because the
          author already drove it green, CI mostly just agrees.
        </p>
        <pre class="term"><code><span class="term-com"># .github/workflows/bastion.yml</span>
<span class="term-prompt">&check;</span> <span class="term-cmd">bastion / gate</span>
<span class="term-out">  single-responsibility</span> <span class="term-out--pass">pass</span>
<span class="term-out">  error-handling       </span> <span class="term-out--pass">pass</span>
<span class="term-out">  release-surface      </span> <span class="term-out--pass">pass</span>
<span class="term-out term-out--pass">merge gate: pass</span></code></pre>
      </article>
    </div>

    <p class="mirror-foot" data-reveal>
      Bastion doesn't own your CI. It runs anywhere code can run, and stays
      portable across the local and GitHub surfaces by keeping them deliberate
      mirror images.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .mirror-grid {
    margin-top: clamp(2rem, 1rem + 3vw, 3rem);
    display: grid;
    gap: 1.25rem;
    align-items: stretch;
    grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1fr);
  }
  @media (min-width: 880px) {
    .mirror-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr auto 1fr;
      align-items: center;
    }
  }

  .surface {
    background: var(--paper-raised);
    border: 1px solid var(--line-strong);
    border-radius: var(--radius-3);
    padding: clamp(1.1rem, 0.8rem + 1vw, 1.5rem);
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-1);
    height: 100%;
  }
  .surface-head {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.7rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }
  .surface-tag {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--steel-deep);
    background: var(--steel-bg);
    border: 1px solid var(--steel-line);
    padding: 0.15em 0.5em;
    border-radius: var(--radius-1);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
  }
  .surface-head h3 {
    font-size: var(--text-md);
  }
  .surface-copy {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    color: var(--ink-2);
    margin-bottom: 1.1rem;
  }

  .term {
    background: var(--ink);
    border-radius: var(--radius-2);
    padding: 0.9rem 1rem;
    overflow-x: auto;
    font-size: 0.76rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }
  .term code {
    color: var(--ink-inverse);
  }
  .term-com {
    color: oklch(0.62 0.02 250);
    font-style: italic;
  }
  .term-prompt {
    color: oklch(0.6 0.1 250);
    user-select: none;
  }
  .term-cmd {
    color: oklch(0.9 0.01 240);
  }
  .term-out {
    color: oklch(0.74 0.012 240);
  }
  .term-out--pass {
    color: oklch(0.74 0.13 150);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .mirror-link {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.6rem;
    justify-content: center;
  }
  @media (min-width: 880px) {
    .mirror-link {
      flex-direction: column;
      height: 100%;
      padding-block: 2rem;
    }
  }
  .mirror-link-line {
    flex: 1;
    height: 1px;
    min-width: 1.5rem;
    background: repeating-linear-gradient(
      to right,
      var(--steel-line) 0 4px,
      transparent 4px 8px
    );
  }
  @media (min-width: 880px) {
    .mirror-link-line {
      width: 1px;
      height: auto;
      background: repeating-linear-gradient(
        to bottom,
        var(--steel-line) 0 4px,
        transparent 4px 8px
      );
    }
  }
  .mirror-link-chip {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    color: var(--steel-deep);
    background: var(--paper);
    border: 1px solid var(--steel-line);
    border-radius: var(--radius-pill);
    padding: 0.3em 0.7em;
    white-space: nowrap;
  }

  .mirror-foot {
    margin-top: clamp(1.75rem, 1rem + 2vw, 2.5rem);
    max-width: var(--measure);
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    color: var(--ink-2);
  }
</style>
